latestIgtvVideos.title: DIY FOR OILY/ACNE PRONE OILY SKIN
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
This is a DIY for all the oily/acne prone oily skin people out there.
This will work very well if you have this skin type. You just have to use it twice or trice a week for 15-20 minutes and you will start seeing results in two weeks.
If you are using any of these ingredients for the first time, DO A PATCH TEST FIRST, if it suits you then only use it.
If you have severe acne consult a dermatologist before using anything on your face.
Ingedients uded:
Multani mitti- One tablespoon
Sandalwood powder- one tablespoon
Neem powder- half a tablespoon
Turmeric- half a tablespoon
Green Tea water- two tablespoon
Mix them well, till the mixture becomes semi liquid, but not runny.
P.S- I know my eyes look puffy. I had a just woke up.
I hope you like this video and found this helpful and if you do please like and share or tag it with someone with oily skin and follow @obscure_makeup for more helpful and fun content.
Stay safe.

latestPosts.caption:
Read the full experience here:

@mattlookcosmetic approached me in June 2024 for a 3-reel collaboration. I delivered the first video (for a gloss) on time — they delayed the launch and asked me to go ahead with the next two products. After uploading the second reel, I asked about payment for the first one… and they started ignoring me.

After several follow-ups, I was told the gloss would launch in 3 months and was offered 3 more reels to “make up for it” and by the time I upload my 5th reel, the gloss will be launched. Naively, I said yes — thinking they genuinely wanted to resolve things. But getting paid for each reel became a battle.

Once 5 videos were uploaded, they cancelled the gloss launch entirely — and still expected the 6th video to be posted. Then their POC approached me for another 6-reel collaboration. This was the stupidest decision I ever made — she begged me, praised my content, apologized repeatedly… and I gave in.

The same patterns repeated:
✨ Products that never launched
✨ Payments super delayed 
✨ Excuses after excuses

I finally cut ties after uploading the 3rd reel from that 6-reel collaboration, as my payments were getting insanely delayed. Plus they sent me another product (A liquid lipstick) which was “supposed” to launch but never did. 

I later learned other creators had the same experience — late payments, poor communication, and zero professionalism.

This isn’t just about money — it’s about respect.
Good products can’t make up for a bad team. Never working with them again. 🚫
